	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Harare - Doctors in Zimbabwe are striking for a second week over pay, working conditions and drug shortages. It's the first major labour dispute since President Mnangagwa took over. Many state run hospitals across the country are struggling financially. Junior doctors say it is frustrating working in them, with a lack of equipment and drugs. Watch the report from Al jazeera here 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  